<p>Go to the <a href="https://djibouti-evisa.com/apply-evisa/"><strong>Djibouti eVisa Application </strong></a>portal and provide your personal details, travel information, and necessary documents like your passport and accommodation details. Ensure your passport is valid for at least six months.</p>

<p>Djibouti, a small but culturally rich country in the <strong>Horn of Africa</strong>, is deeply influenced by <strong>Islamic traditions</strong> and <strong>African customs</strong>. Religion plays a central role in the <strong>daily lives, laws, and social norms</strong> of Djiboutians. While <strong>Islam is the dominant religion</strong>, the country is known for its <strong>religious tolerance and peaceful coexistence</strong> among different faiths. Djibouti is predominantly Muslim, with Islam shaping daily life and customs. Visitors should respect local traditions. A<a href="https://online.djibouti-evisa.com/"><strong>Djibouti eVisa</strong></a> is required for entry and can be easily obtained online.</p>
